      "content": "i get that, but even looking at the academic side of things, it seems like modern legal scholars mostly treat originalism as a political tactic rather than a real scholarly framework. wouldn't you say it's more of a philosophical workaround for when judges want to reach a specific outcome, rather than a consistent method like living constitutionalism?",
